sql:
SELECT blade_size, description, material, tooth_count, blade_thickness, coating
FROM saw_blades
WHERE manufacturer = 'Manufacturer A';

external_knowledge:
- "stars" metaphorically refers to customers;
- "outshone the average radiance" means total spent is greater than the average total spent;
- "constellation of our spending galaxy" metaphorically represents the database of customer spending.

sql:
SELECT blade_id, price
FROM pricing
WHERE price > (SELECT AVG(price) FROM pricing);

external_knowledge:
- The term "inventory health status" refers to the relationship between the current stock level and the reorder level;
- A saw blade with a stock level above the reorder level is considered to have sufficient stock;
- A saw blade with a stock level equal to the reorder level is at a critical stock level, indicating it's time to consider restocking;
- A saw blade with a stock level below the reorder level requires immediate attention and restocking.

sql:
SELECT blade_id, COUNT(blade_id) AS total_sales
FROM sales_data
GROUP BY blade_id;

SELECT c.customer_name, sd.sale_date, sd.total_price
FROM customers c
JOIN sales_data sd ON c.customer_id = sd.customer_id;

SELECT AVG(tooth_count) AS avg_tooth_count, manufacturer
FROM saw_blades
GROUP BY manufacturer;

SELECT program_id, discount, required_points, description, valid_from, valid_to, max_discount, redeemable_products
FROM loyalty_program
WHERE discount = '20%';

SELECT AVG(price) 
FROM pricing 
WHERE blade_id = 1;
